THE WAVE

3
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:04,400
Good morning.

4
00:02:09,655 --> 00:02:11,655
Good morning.

5
00:02:16,805 --> 00:02:19,605
Yes exactly, and always be on the watch
for the kids smoking in the schoolyard, OK?

6
00:02:22,339 --> 00:02:24,282
<i>Hello, my precious.</i>

7
00:02:24,283 --> 00:02:25,899
Well, my rocker?

8
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:28,350
You know we teachers are
lazy, don't spoil our image.

9
00:02:28,351 --> 00:02:30,248
I only need to copy a few worksheets.

10
00:02:30,249 --> 00:02:31,305
Have you already been at Kohlhage's?

11
00:02:31,306 --> 00:02:32,454
No, why?

12
00:02:32,455 --> 00:02:34,204
Oh, she has asked for you.

13
00:02:34,205 --> 00:02:36,205
Then I'll go.

14
00:02:38,152 --> 00:02:41,076
Autocracy? I thought it was very
clear deal that I'll do Anarchy course.

15
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:43,550
Dieter Wieland just
presented his concept to me.

16
00:02:43,551 --> 00:02:45,952
He spent whole week preparing
hard he mastered it perfectly...

17
00:02:46,165 --> 00:02:47,960
...and I just started to
prepare over the weekend.

18
00:02:47,961 --> 00:02:49,949
Yes, bit late, right.

19
00:02:49,950 --> 00:02:52,300
Wieland, Wieland have no
idea at all about the topic.

20
00:02:53,150 --> 00:02:56,490
I've studied in Berlin, I have lived
five years in the last house in Kreuzberg.

21
00:02:56,900 --> 00:02:59,530
1st May, always there. So who is
better suitable to do it, than me?

22
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:02,866
If you really care so much then you can ask
Mr Wieland  whether he want to switch with you.

23
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:07,580
Could you do it again...

24
00:03:08,150 --> 00:03:10,150
You make a deal with him yourself.

25
00:03:14,650 --> 00:03:16,650
Mr. Wieland.

26
00:03:16,749 --> 00:03:18,749
Mr Wenger.

27
00:03:18,850 --> 00:03:20,850
It is about the issue
for the project week.

28
00:03:20,873 --> 00:03:21,899
Yes, and?

29
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:23,651
I wanted to ask you if you could switch?

30
00:03:23,652 --> 00:03:25,471
I have Autocracy.

31
00:03:25,472 --> 00:03:27,472
Alea iacta est.

32
00:03:29,450 --> 00:03:31,450
The die is cast.

33
00:03:31,830 --> 00:03:34,119
You know very well how much
I would like to teach Anarchy.

34
00:03:34,279 --> 00:03:36,249
Seems even too likely to me.

35
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:40,965
In the Project Week we focus on teaching the students
about the benefits of the democracy for the world.

36
00:03:42,165 --> 00:03:44,188
How to mix Molotov cocktails...

37
00:03:44,462 --> 00:03:46,717
...maybe only in the Chemistry lessons.

38
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:49,160
Have a Nice day.

39
00:03:51,608 --> 00:03:52,949
I loved you...

40
00:03:52,950 --> 00:03:54,650
...you have betrayed me.

41
00:03:54,651 --> 00:03:57,503
But the dream of life,
of love, confidence,...

42
00:03:58,050 --> 00:04:00,470
...this once real dream
I have not forgotten.

43
00:04:00,707 --> 00:04:03,450
I want to build it
up with my billion,...

44
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:05,550
...change the past by destroying you.

45
00:04:06,102 --> 00:04:07,749
Honey!

46
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:09,772
I thank you for the bouquete.

47
00:04:10,550 --> 00:04:13,350
Would anything change, if I
lie in a box in Golden Apostle?

48
00:04:13,439 --> 00:04:14,539
He is really ridiculous, man.

49
00:04:14,540 --> 00:04:15,995
Not true?

50
00:04:15,996 --> 00:04:17,996
Do you really know.

51
00:04:21,555 --> 00:04:24,008
I will take you in your coffin to Capri.

52
00:04:24,171 --> 00:04:26,155
Moment, he says quite something else.

53
00:04:26,156 --> 00:04:27,568
Now I want to say it so.

54
00:04:27,569 --> 00:04:30,346
Ferdi dude, but this one time we wanted to do
it through the End, without interruption, right?

55
00:04:30,551 --> 00:04:31,729
You have stopped it.

56
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:33,449
Supreme Theatre rule, Karo :

57
00:04:33,450 --> 00:04:34,899
"Always continue."

58
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:37,050
Dennis, you wanted to compare
play's critique for capitalism...

59
00:04:37,051 --> 00:04:39,051
...to current globalisation issues.

60
00:04:39,100 --> 00:04:41,850
Yes, and that is why I also show
the play in more contemporary manner.

61
00:04:41,851 --> 00:04:43,979
It is okay if it is
contemporary, but this is silly.

62
00:04:43,980 --> 00:04:45,349
You can not enforce it.

63
00:04:45,350 --> 00:04:47,930
Yes, we actually play Drrenmatt,
not some rubbish comedy club piece.

64
00:04:49,350 --> 00:04:53,050
I thank you for the wreaths,
the chrysanthemums and roses.

65
00:04:53,150 --> 00:04:54,774
Noble.

66
00:04:54,775 --> 00:04:56,149
Hey, that sounds totally shitty!

67
00:04:56,150 --> 00:04:58,525
Sorry, I'm most certainly not
going to to say it in that way.

68
00:04:58,526 --> 00:04:59,851
Forget it.

69
00:04:59,852 --> 00:05:01,699
Quite simply, if Ferdi isn't
going to follow the script,...

70
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:03,700
...then I can also not play.

71
00:05:05,150 --> 00:05:07,150
He is' still young square.

72
00:05:08,150 --> 00:05:09,799
Oh man, I'm not in the mood any more.

73
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:10,750
I am leaving now, are you going with me?

74
00:05:10,751 --> 00:05:12,271
It's really better, if...

75
00:05:12,272 --> 00:05:14,272
If the piece is played
much more serious.

76
00:05:14,450 --> 00:05:16,450
Yes, there's simply no sense
if each one does what he wants.

77
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:19,750
Are you coming to the game today?

78
00:05:20,250 --> 00:05:22,250
Lisa and I have yet to learn Spanish.

79
00:05:22,352 --> 00:05:24,352
Still have the whole afternoon.

80
00:05:24,450 --> 00:05:26,450
Well, what courses
did you registered for?

81
00:05:26,705 --> 00:05:28,054
Entered?

82
00:05:28,055 --> 00:05:29,749
Yes, for the Project Week.

83
00:05:29,750 --> 00:05:30,949
They hanged the lists already?

84
00:05:30,950 --> 00:05:32,160
Sure.

85
00:05:32,161 --> 00:05:33,242
I want to take Autocracy.

86
00:05:33,243 --> 00:05:35,243
Yes cool, I'll be there, too.

87
00:05:35,850 --> 00:05:37,169
Then I must....

88
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:38,371
Would you sign me in too?

89
00:05:38,372 --> 00:05:39,819
For what?

90
00:05:39,820 --> 00:05:41,613
Well, for that one you are taking too.

91
00:05:41,614 --> 00:05:43,614
Okay.

92
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,800
See you.

93
00:06:09,051 --> 00:06:10,774
Now once again pull
yourself together, okay?

94
00:06:10,775 --> 00:06:12,339
Now i want to see a
real, aggressive play.

95
00:06:12,340 --> 00:06:14,949
Pay attention to defense and
go for Konter cover, okay?

96
00:06:15,261 --> 00:06:18,106
For your knowledge, we have now
8 minutes, we can do it, okay?

97
00:06:18,202 --> 00:06:20,253
Marco. Marco, this
one goes for you, too.

98
00:06:20,350 --> 00:06:22,350
Yes, work together.

99
00:06:23,450 --> 00:06:25,450
Yes, pay attention to the defence.

100
00:06:27,261 --> 00:06:30,014
And hold together, play
together. Okay? 8 minutes to go.

101
00:06:30,701 --> 00:06:32,701
Once more, now come, come, go.

102
00:06:40,361 --> 00:06:42,361
Watch out!

103
00:06:43,325 --> 00:06:45,325
Beautiful, beautiful
go to the front now!

104
00:06:48,702 --> 00:06:50,702
Beautiful, Marco!

105
00:06:52,950 --> 00:06:54,965
Give it!Give the Game! Sinan is free!

106
00:06:54,966 --> 00:06:56,966
- Marco, I am free!
- Trust me just once.

107
00:07:00,651 --> 00:07:02,395
Damn it, what are you doing again!?

108
00:07:02,396 --> 00:07:04,396
Sinan was free!

109
00:07:04,550 --> 00:07:06,570
...free for a date, or what?

110
00:07:33,272 --> 00:07:35,272
What's wrong with you ?

111
00:08:29,530 --> 00:08:31,530
Martin, now tell us, yes?

112
00:08:31,730 --> 00:08:34,908
Tell me, against what can
we actually rebel today?

113
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:37,370
Nothing has any value anymore, yes?

114
00:08:37,371 --> 00:08:40,803
Everyone has only his...
His own pleasure in mind.

115
00:08:41,100 --> 00:08:43,049
What our generation is missing...

116
00:08:43,050 --> 00:08:45,564
...is a common goal...
that will bring us together.

117
00:08:45,565 --> 00:08:48,000
That is the spirit of
our times, get a grip.

118
00:08:48,481 --> 00:08:50,518
The most googled person
in Internet is Who?

119
00:08:51,550 --> 00:08:53,550
Paris "Fucking" Hilton.

120
00:08:53,550 --> 00:08:56,150
- Oh, shit.
- Without shit.

121
00:08:57,565 --> 00:08:59,975
Hey, let it out. It will be better.

122
00:09:08,472 --> 00:09:10,472
Stolti.

123
00:09:13,095 --> 00:09:15,095
And Stolti, do you have some dope today?

124
00:09:15,255 --> 00:09:17,255
Yes, of course.

125
00:09:21,051 --> 00:09:22,636
And it's really one, or?

126
00:09:22,637 --> 00:09:23,518
Of course,...

127
00:09:23,519 --> 00:09:25,519
...colleague of mine brought
it from Holland yesterday.

128
00:09:26,755 --> 00:09:29,125
Is your brain completely burned out, why
are u running around with so much grass.

129
00:09:30,150 --> 00:09:32,150
I will worry about the cops myself.

130
00:09:34,450 --> 00:09:36,450
What do u want for it?

131
00:09:38,705 --> 00:09:40,154
Nothing.

132
00:09:40,155 --> 00:09:42,155
- What?
- I'll give you for free.

133
00:09:42,851 --> 00:09:44,851
You are my homies.

134
00:09:51,250 --> 00:09:53,250
<i>Monday</i>

135
00:10:13,172 --> 00:10:14,654
Baby!

136
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:16,655
The water is totally
cool, probably 16 degrees.

137
00:10:18,052 --> 00:10:20,052
Wouldn't you like to swim for a while?

138
00:10:20,183 --> 00:10:21,915
That would be good for you.

139
00:10:21,916 --> 00:10:23,704
Maybe later.

140
00:10:23,705 --> 00:10:25,374
How is your shoulder?

141
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:26,449
Is back in normal.

142
00:10:26,450 --> 00:10:28,450
You should not overload it?

143
00:10:28,872 --> 00:10:30,872
No, no.

144
00:10:31,872 --> 00:10:33,149
Do you want some coffee?

145
00:10:33,150 --> 00:10:35,150
Yes. Thank you.

146
00:10:40,355 --> 00:10:42,355
Good morning.

147
00:10:43,251 --> 00:10:44,374
Is there something for free?

148
00:10:44,375 --> 00:10:46,375
- All fresh, Rainer?
- I hope.

149
00:10:47,037 --> 00:10:49,037
- Good morning, Rainer.
- Sinan.

150
00:10:51,151 --> 00:10:52,843
Quite frankly I'm a bit surprised...

151
00:10:52,844 --> 00:10:55,273
...that so many are interested
in the Autocracy topic.

152
00:10:55,351 --> 00:10:57,351
In your place, I would
rather pick Anarchy.

153
00:10:57,527 --> 00:10:58,534
By "old fart" Wieland?

154
00:10:58,535 --> 00:11:00,535
These are your own words.

155
00:11:03,302 --> 00:11:05,302
Well...

156
00:11:16,472 --> 00:11:18,472
Autocracy, what is it?

157
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:22,640
Come on, you have chosen that topic.

158
00:11:22,850 --> 00:11:24,880
You must know at least
something about it.

159
00:11:25,272 --> 00:11:27,272
Well, hopefully it will
not put more stress on us.

160
00:11:28,850 --> 00:11:31,646
Seriously, what is the meaning
of autocratic forms of government?

161
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:33,799
Maybe something like monarchy?

162
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:35,149
Not necessarily.

163
00:11:35,150 --> 00:11:37,049
Ferdi, do u have any
thoughts about this?

164
00:11:37,050 --> 00:11:39,050
It's a car race in
craters. (Auto-Cracy)

165
00:11:40,322 --> 00:11:42,322
Now that was really
very resourceful answer.

166
00:11:44,231 --> 00:11:45,849
Dictatorship perhaps?

167
00:11:45,850 --> 00:11:47,699
Among other things, yes. Karo?

168
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:50,323
I think the autocracy
is if an individual...

169
00:11:50,405 --> 00:11:52,405
...or a group dominate the mass.

170
00:11:52,538 --> 00:11:53,949
Exactly.

171
00:11:53,950 --> 00:11:55,876
Autocracy derives from the Greek...

172
00:11:55,877 --> 00:11:57,347
...and means self-rule.

173
00:11:57,348 --> 00:12:01,416
Also, "Auto" from yourself and
"Kratia" from to dominate, Power.

174
00:12:01,465 --> 00:12:05,283
In an autocracy an individual or a
group involved in the Government has...

175
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:08,054
...so much power that the laws
can change how they want it.

176
00:12:08,349 --> 00:12:10,349
Do you have examples
of such systems?

177
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:14,428
We need to spend the
week doing something.

178
00:12:14,927 --> 00:12:16,137
Oh, come on, you can think
of some form of dictatorship.

179
00:12:16,138 --> 00:12:17,350
Third Reich.

180
00:12:17,351 --> 00:12:19,194
Ah no, not again.

181
00:12:19,195 --> 00:12:21,195
So, I did not choose
this topic for myself....

182
00:12:21,951 --> 00:12:23,951
I've printed out a few
notice for you.

183
00:12:24,139 --> 00:12:25,505
Not that shit all over again.

184
00:12:25,506 --> 00:12:27,399
Oh man, but it's an important issue.

185
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:29,965
Nazi Germany was shit.
Slowly, even I understand that"

186
00:12:30,152 --> 00:12:31,899
Exactly, damned Nazis!

187
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:34,609
- It happened here so it's not going to
happen anymore. - Oh yes, and the Neo-Nazis?

188
00:12:34,610 --> 00:12:37,350
We can not permanently feel guilty
for something that we did not do.

189
00:12:37,551 --> 00:12:38,724
It is not just the guilt...

190
00:12:38,725 --> 00:12:41,706
...it is also a fact that we, with our
history have a certain responsibility.

191
00:12:41,864 --> 00:12:43,864
So, I am a Turk!

192
00:12:44,150 --> 00:12:45,902
Clear responsibility, yes, but
I mean everybody knows this.

193
00:12:45,903 --> 00:12:46,903
Everyone  who?

194
00:12:46,904 --> 00:12:48,534
Well, perhaps only few
dumb Easterners don't...

195
00:12:48,535 --> 00:12:50,839
What does this mean ? I'm
also from East Germany.

196
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:52,749
You exactly know what
I mean, here bald heads.

197
00:12:52,750 --> 00:12:54,250
Rainer, can't we talk
about anything else?

198
00:12:54,251 --> 00:12:56,523
- What?
- Let talk about the Bush administration.

199
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:58,880
Wait a minute, It just
started to be interesting.

200
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:02,138
So, your opinion is that the dictatorship
in Germany is no longer possible, yes?

201
00:13:02,195 --> 00:13:04,195
No way, we are much
more enlightened now.

202
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:07,750
Marco, what do you mean?

203
00:13:09,850 --> 00:13:11,850
I do not know.

204
00:13:21,509 --> 00:13:23,509
Well, we will have ten minute break.

205
00:13:44,450 --> 00:13:46,450
What's going on here?

206
00:13:46,855 --> 00:13:49,438
We have rearranged the tables, now
everybody has at least some place.

207
00:13:49,506 --> 00:13:51,506
Bring your tables behind.

208
00:13:59,441 --> 00:14:02,297
Possibly we can manage the
Project Week in a way as we want.

209
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:05,550
I suggest that we loosen
that whole thing a bit.

210
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:07,550
Has anyone anything against it?

211
00:14:08,834 --> 00:14:10,834
Very good.

212
00:14:11,461 --> 00:14:14,497
What is the basic foundation
for autocratic system?

213
00:14:15,050 --> 00:14:16,699
Dennis?

214
00:14:16,700 --> 00:14:17,800
An ideology.

215
00:14:17,801 --> 00:14:19,249
Yes, what else?

216
00:14:19,250 --> 00:14:20,678
Control.

217
00:14:20,679 --> 00:14:21,752
Monitoring.

218
00:14:21,753 --> 00:14:23,753
You think a bit too far.

219
00:14:23,850 --> 00:14:25,654
Dissatisfaction.

220
00:14:25,655 --> 00:14:27,604
Interesting.

221
00:14:27,605 --> 00:14:29,772
But what I mean is: What is the
thing that any dictatorship has?

222
00:14:29,872 --> 00:14:31,654
We have already spoken
about it earlier.

223
00:14:31,655 --> 00:14:33,149
A leader, man

224
00:14:33,150 --> 00:14:33,949
A leader?

225
00:14:33,950 --> 00:14:36,097
Yes, bringing out a word leader (Fuhrer)
will only make this discussion harder.

226
00:14:36,158 --> 00:14:38,519
But each dictatorship
has a central leader.

227
00:14:39,350 --> 00:14:41,983
We can play a game here. So who
could be a leader here, among us?

228
00:14:42,405 --> 00:14:43,651
You, as a teacher. Of course.

229
00:14:43,652 --> 00:14:45,406
- I?
- Who else?

230
00:14:45,407 --> 00:14:47,882
Well, I was hoping that somebody
else wanted to start first, perhaps.

231
00:14:52,150 --> 00:14:54,150
I'm gonna' do it... I'm
going to be your Leader!

232
00:14:54,552 --> 00:14:55,808
Forget it.

233
00:14:55,809 --> 00:14:57,639
Rainer, you do it

234
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:58,639
Okay, so we agree.

235
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:01,297
Who want to support me during the
Project Week as your leading figure?

236
00:15:01,813 --> 00:15:03,813
- Of what use can it be for us?
- Just wait a while.

237
00:15:04,650 --> 00:15:06,650
I'm going to ask in another
way, who is against? Against?

238
00:15:08,350 --> 00:15:10,350
Abstention?

239
00:15:11,149 --> 00:15:11,948
Well.

240
00:15:11,949 --> 00:15:13,949
Rainer Heil!

241
00:15:14,127 --> 00:15:16,127
Such a leading figure deserves respect.

242
00:15:17,427 --> 00:15:20,703
Therefore, I would like to be addressed
as Mr Wenger during that whole time.

243
00:15:20,850 --> 00:15:22,049
Mr Wenger.

244
00:15:22,050 --> 00:15:24,050
Now he is becoming megalomaniac.

245
00:15:24,350 --> 00:15:26,254
Hey, didn't we just voted, right?

246
00:15:26,255 --> 00:15:27,864
What do you want from me, Easterner?

247
00:15:27,865 --> 00:15:29,650
Now, come do it with us.

248
00:15:29,651 --> 00:15:31,651
You are not telling me what to do!

249
00:15:32,570 --> 00:15:34,349
Watch your language, you dork.

250
00:15:34,350 --> 00:15:37,456
Now please calm down. Come, take all
the stuff from your tables. Everything.

251
00:15:38,150 --> 00:15:40,682
And from now on, only one who Is
permitted to speak, will speak.

252
00:15:40,900 --> 00:15:42,249
Yes, Mr Wenger.

253
00:15:42,250 --> 00:15:44,250
Did I give you the permission to talk?

254
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:45,560
No.

255
00:15:45,561 --> 00:15:48,049
And one more thing, anybody
that speaks must stand up too.

256
00:15:48,262 --> 00:15:49,356
Isn't that a bit too much?

257
