Marco, man, open your eyes.

1011
01:00:47,516 --> 01:00:49,560
The Wave is becoming
one really weird thing.

1012
01:00:51,400 --> 01:00:53,199
You are involved too much in it.

1013
01:00:53,200 --> 01:00:55,200
Oh, really? Then take a look at this.

1014
01:00:58,022 --> 01:01:00,022
Just the fact that the pages looks like.

1015
01:01:00,101 --> 01:01:01,598
Yes, Tim made them.

1016
01:01:01,599 --> 01:01:03,599
He is always exaggerating.

1017
01:01:05,200 --> 01:01:06,104
Here...

1018
01:01:06,105 --> 01:01:08,583
"Yesterday, some guy wearing a white
shirt pressed on me and said that...

1019
01:01:08,600 --> 01:01:11,250
...unless I join The Wave,
I will loose all my friends...

1020
01:01:11,300 --> 01:01:13,099
...because all of them
would join in soon.

1021
01:01:13,100 --> 01:01:14,801
I just simply said that
I will think about it.

1022
01:01:14,802 --> 01:01:17,489
And than, he aggressively said
that it might be too late."

1023
01:01:18,355 --> 01:01:20,021
Too late for what, Marco?

1024
01:01:20,022 --> 01:01:22,350
Don't you understand what is going on
here? Students are under pressure here.

1025
01:01:23,506 --> 01:01:25,860
Yes, but the involvement is anonymous.

1026
01:01:26,507 --> 01:01:28,700
- How do you know if they don't cheat on it?
- Cheat?

1027
01:01:29,412 --> 01:01:31,399
Leon didn't let one
Six-grader into the school...

1028
01:01:31,400 --> 01:01:33,488
...only because he did not want to
perform your stupid Wave greeting.

1029
01:01:36,002 --> 01:01:38,510
I'm sorry, but your brother
always acts little bit strange.

1030
01:01:38,511 --> 01:01:39,049
But no only that...

1031
01:01:39,050 --> 01:01:42,053
...they even treat me like a leper
because I don't wear white shirt.

1032
01:01:43,401 --> 01:01:44,921
Why do not you just wear it?

1033
01:01:44,922 --> 01:01:46,922
Simply because I do not want.

1034
01:01:47,144 --> 01:01:50,416
But I want, because
The Wave means to me.

1035
01:01:51,106 --> 01:01:53,106
Means what?

1036
01:01:53,285 --> 01:01:55,285
Community.

1037
01:01:56,322 --> 01:01:59,130
You know that feeling very well, you
belong to a healthy family, I do not.

1038
01:02:04,866 --> 01:02:06,866
Going with me or not?

1039
01:02:13,167 --> 01:02:14,667
Can I help you sir?

1040
01:02:14,668 --> 01:02:15,865
What are you doing here?

1041
01:02:15,866 --> 01:02:17,380
I need to protect you.

1042
01:02:17,381 --> 01:02:18,599
You need to do what?

1043
01:02:18,600 --> 01:02:20,268
I want to be your bodyguard.

1044
01:02:20,269 --> 01:02:22,269
What do I need a
bodyguard? Tim, go home.

1045
01:02:23,304 --> 01:02:25,074
What am I supposed to go home for?

1046
01:02:25,075 --> 01:02:27,075
Nobody is Interested
for me there, anyway.

1047
01:02:34,808 --> 01:02:36,499
So, if you have any problem feel
free to come to talk to me...

1048
01:02:36,500 --> 01:02:38,555
...but I do not need
no bodyguards, okay?

1049
01:02:42,114 --> 01:02:44,114
Come with me.

1050
01:02:55,322 --> 01:02:57,322
- Hello, precious!
- Hello!

1051
01:02:57,662 --> 01:02:59,662
What did Kohlhage want?

1052
01:03:02,500 --> 01:03:03,974
Hi, Tim.

1053
01:03:03,975 --> 01:03:05,099
Hello, Mrs. Wenger.

1054
01:03:05,100 --> 01:03:07,248
- Rainer, can I speak briefly with you.
- Yes, of course.

1055
01:03:10,619 --> 01:03:12,367
What's this supposed to be?

1056
01:03:12,368 --> 01:03:15,054
It was not my idea, I have not invited
him. Suddenly he was just standing there.

1057
01:03:15,715 --> 01:03:17,715
He has nobody to take
care for him back at home.

1058
01:03:18,599 --> 01:03:20,470
I had different idea about this.

1059
01:03:20,471 --> 01:03:22,497
Come, lets eat together, I
will send him home later, okay?

1060
01:03:24,517 --> 01:03:26,111
Mr Wenger...

1061
01:03:26,112 --> 01:03:28,112
...do happened to have
little bit more ginger?

1062
01:03:28,335 --> 01:03:30,335
Only then it will be really delicious.

1063
01:04:20,500 --> 01:04:23,203
- It is really cool here.
- I told you.

1064
01:04:24,801 --> 01:04:27,863
- Say, what is actually going on with Karo?
- Why?

1065
01:04:28,211 --> 01:04:30,799
She was in the editorial and
had put a lot of stress on us.

1066
01:04:31,200 --> 01:04:32,499
Because of The Wave?

1067
01:04:32,500 --> 01:04:35,599
Yes, she wanted all student's personal data
to be able to send some emails and so on.

1068
01:04:36,207 --> 01:04:39,590
- Gross, no joke?
- No.

1069
01:04:49,844 --> 01:04:51,808
<i>e-mail being sent.</i>

1070
01:04:51,809 --> 01:04:53,809
<i>e-mail canceled.</i>

1071
01:05:08,193 --> 01:05:09,099
<i>No LAN connection.</i>

1072
01:05:09,100 --> 01:05:10,314
Shit!

1073
01:05:10,315 --> 01:05:12,443
Well, first we thought of Paris...

1074
01:05:12,673 --> 01:05:14,906
...and then to Balaton lake. Balaton?

1075
01:05:15,300 --> 01:05:18,732
But Italy, good food, beautiful women.

1076
01:05:18,800 --> 01:05:20,599
You always need more and more.

1077
01:05:20,600 --> 01:05:23,090
And than I thought, why don't
you sir join us as a supervisor.

1078
01:05:24,403 --> 01:05:25,599
Let's see, Tim.

1079
01:05:25,600 --> 01:05:27,981
Tuscany, also, it would be superb.

1080
01:05:28,300 --> 01:05:30,300
You know Tim, Rainer can
not decide on his own.

1081
01:05:30,594 --> 01:05:33,000
Yes, but I am sure all
students would support it.

1082
01:05:33,100 --> 01:05:35,100
And if not, we could
organize signature action.

1083
01:05:38,011 --> 01:05:40,011
It was really nice evening, Tim. Really.

1084
01:05:40,600 --> 01:05:43,595
But Anke and I, we would like to be alone,
we have a couple of things to discuss.

1085
01:05:44,403 --> 01:05:46,403
Sure.

1086
01:05:53,163 --> 01:05:55,163
Thanks Tim. See you tomorrow.

1087
01:06:23,300 --> 01:06:25,300
Do you know the story of "Six hikers?

1088
01:06:25,499 --> 01:06:27,132
No.

1089
01:06:27,133 --> 01:06:28,799
My father told me.

1090
01:06:28,800 --> 01:06:30,800
At the spot where the Great
Lakes joins together...

1091
01:06:31,200 --> 01:06:34,204
...they always find half a dozen of
drowned corpses floating in water.

1092
01:06:35,269 --> 01:06:38,466
Again and again, being seen by divers
and held as just a recent accident...

1093
01:06:39,000 --> 01:06:41,599
...until they realize that the
clothes on them are from the Eighties.

1094
01:06:43,711 --> 01:06:45,711
Most of them are suicides.

1095
01:06:46,000 --> 01:06:47,799
But that is scariest...

1096
01:06:47,800 --> 01:06:52,320
...thing is that the current always brings them
to the same spot where they actually drowned.

1097
01:06:52,800 --> 01:06:55,850
Just like they are looking
for redemption or justice.

1098
01:06:56,400 --> 01:06:58,500
Therefore, fishermen calls
them "The six walkers."

1099
01:07:00,400 --> 01:07:02,400
Understood.

1100
01:07:17,100 --> 01:07:19,575
- Hey, can I?
- Yes.

1101
01:07:26,055 --> 01:07:28,055
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

1102
01:07:39,966 --> 01:07:41,966
It's really nice here, right?

1103
01:07:44,301 --> 01:07:46,301
I never wanna leave this place.

1104
01:07:46,601 --> 01:07:48,601
Who said you would?

1105
01:07:50,409 --> 01:07:52,603
Yeah, right.

1106
01:07:54,133 --> 01:07:56,133
After the final exams
first to enter university.

1107
01:07:57,122 --> 01:07:59,122
I don't even know which one.

1108
01:08:00,969 --> 01:08:02,935
I could pretty well imagine myself...

1109
01:08:02,936 --> 01:08:04,936
...having some normal job...

1110
01:08:06,100 --> 01:08:09,277
...marrying nice woman,
having two-three kids...

1111
01:08:11,600 --> 01:08:14,585
...and live in quiet neighbourhood
for the rest of my days.

1112
01:08:18,926 --> 01:08:21,707
- Do you think that's stupid?
- No, not at all.

1113
01:08:43,766 --> 01:08:46,099
Hey, turn the music down
and come here everybody.

1114
01:08:50,522 --> 01:08:52,522
Where is Marco?

1115
01:08:52,795 --> 01:08:54,795
Marco!

1116
01:08:56,016 --> 01:08:58,016
Yes, come here!

1117
01:08:58,382 --> 01:09:00,382
Marco!

1118
01:09:00,674 --> 01:09:02,674
What is it?

1119
01:09:08,305 --> 01:09:12,931
Good! First of all, it's really
cool that you are all here.

1120
01:09:13,000 --> 01:09:15,000
Really great!

1121
01:09:15,615 --> 01:09:18,152
And second, as you all know,
we are playing a game against...

1122
01:09:18,500 --> 01:09:22,088
..."bulls" from the Ernst
Barlach Comprehensive School.

1123
01:09:22,089 --> 01:09:23,644
All of you must come!

1124
01:09:23,645 --> 01:09:26,322
It would be really cool if all of
you come tomorrow and support us!

1125
01:09:26,391 --> 01:09:29,338
Also, tomorrow at 3 p.m.
at the swimming pool!

1126
01:09:29,592 --> 01:09:30,892
You are really great!

1127
01:09:30,893 --> 01:09:33,459
You must bring all of your friends,
and better they all wear white shirts!

1128
01:09:33,494 --> 01:09:34,399
Everybody!

1129
01:09:34,400 --> 01:09:36,879
The enemy should feel
the power of The Wave!

1130
01:09:38,422 --> 01:09:40,422
Wave!

1131
01:11:32,901 --> 01:11:35,807
<i>Friday</i>

1132
01:12:01,975 --> 01:12:04,389
<i>What does this sign means?</i>

1133
01:12:12,750 --> 01:12:14,750
Good morning, Mr Wenger.

1134
01:12:16,705 --> 01:12:18,599
Say, what is actually wrong with you?

1135
01:12:18,600 --> 01:12:20,538
You can not simply
disappear for all night long.

1136
01:12:20,539 --> 01:12:22,766
Do you actually know what kind of
consequences I will need to face?

1137
01:12:26,766 --> 01:12:28,766
Shit!

1138
01:12:29,099 --> 01:12:31,099
That is one of these
anarchistic fuckers.

1139
01:12:31,315 --> 01:12:33,315
Are you now convinced that
you will be needing protection.

1140
01:12:33,943 --> 01:12:36,269
- Hey, you bum, what's up?
- Yeah, everything good.

1141
01:12:40,100 --> 01:12:41,299
...we have them all.

1142
01:12:41,300 --> 01:12:42,496
Good.

1143
01:12:42,497 --> 01:12:45,300
We all know who might be
responsible for this crap.

1144
01:12:46,866 --> 01:12:48,298
We don't have any evidence.

1145
01:12:48,299 --> 01:12:50,299
Marco, please.

1146
01:12:53,802 --> 01:12:55,727
Marco...

1147
01:12:55,728 --> 01:12:57,728
...you also want The Wave
to keep going on, right?

1148
01:12:59,066 --> 01:13:01,066
Yes, I'm gonna talk to her...

1149
01:13:02,299 --> 01:13:04,299
...but after the game, okay?

1150
01:13:05,533 --> 01:13:07,533
What are we supposed to
do with all these notes?

1151
01:13:07,700 --> 01:13:09,700
Destroy them.

1152
01:13:16,365 --> 01:13:18,365
Everything OK?

1153
01:13:21,800 --> 01:13:23,699
Have no clue who it was!

1154
01:13:23,700 --> 01:13:25,399
I don't even want to know
how did you get up there...

1155
01:13:25,400 --> 01:13:27,400
...but one thing is clear,
that was extremely dangerous!

1156
01:13:30,399 --> 01:13:32,466
In the past I did some bad shit
myself, you can believe me on that.

1157
01:13:34,705 --> 01:13:36,705
But in this case,
this joke went too far!

1158
01:13:37,301 --> 01:13:39,708
- Is that clear?
- Yes, Mr Wenger.

1159
01:13:45,506 --> 01:13:47,506
Sit down!

1160
01:13:49,412 --> 01:13:52,966
I want you all to write down about
your experiences with The Wave.

1161
01:13:53,678 --> 01:13:55,750
And by the end of the class I
want to have them on my desk!

1162
01:13:59,601 --> 01:14:01,601
Now go on, begin!

1163
01:14:29,912 --> 01:14:31,912
The time is up.

1164
01:14:38,868 --> 01:14:40,100
Later, Mr Wenger.

1165
01:14:40,101 --> 01:14:45,149
Oh yes, incidentally, this does not mean that I'm not
going to be pleased seeing some of you during the game.

1166
01:14:45,555 --> 01:14:47,555
We will need your support.

1167
01:14:52,606 --> 01:14:56,375
Mr Wenger, I know who draw
graffiti on the City Hall.

1168
01:14:57,177 --> 01:14:59,738
Tim, have I asked you to give me the
names of those who are responsible?

1169
01:15:00,600 --> 01:15:01,800
Actually I don't want
to know who it was...

1170
01:15:01,801 --> 01:15:04,716
...because if I knew, I would have to
inform School principle and the police.

1171
01:15:05,000 --> 01:15:07,000
Actually this is a collateral damage.

1172
01:15:07,755 --> 01:15:11,412
I hope that you had learned over this week that it
is better to work together and not against each other.

1173
01:15:12,141 --> 01:15:15,577
You especially, should be aware of
the fact that you can not fight alone.

1174
01:15:18,703 --> 01:15:20,703
I would be pleased if you
come to the game today.

1175
01:15:21,477 --> 01:15:23,477
Okay?

1176
01:15:24,750 --> 01:15:26,750
Okay.

1177
01:16:00,488 --> 01:16:01,503
Come on!

1178
01:16:01,504 --> 01:16:03,504
Yes, now play forward!

1179
01:16:03,610 --> 01:16:05,610
Marco, go forward!
What are you doing?

1180
01:16:08,603 --> 01:16:10,890
Yes! Superb!

1181
01:16:16,891 --> 01:16:18,099
I can not let you in.

1182
01:16:18,100 --> 01:16:19,099
What, why not?

1183
01:16:19,100 --> 01:16:20,893
Get yourself a white shirt,
there are still some left outside.

1184
01:16:20,894 --> 01:16:22,894
I don't want your shitty Wave shirt!

1185
01:16:23,100 --> 01:16:25,074
Everybody has one,
don't yell about it.

1186
01:16:25,075 --> 01:16:27,075
You are loosing your mind.

1187
01:16:27,178 --> 01:16:29,178
We have the right side blocked.

1188
01:16:29,656 --> 01:16:31,656
You guys are really missing
some screws in your heads.

1189
01:16:46,600 --> 01:16:48,600
Defence, get closer!

1190
01:16:50,700 --> 01:16:52,700
Go, forward now! Forward!

1191
01:17:01,869 --> 01:17:04,447
Yes! Very good, very good.

1192
01:17:05,300 --> 01:17:07,448
- And, what do you say now?
- Shut you mouth, dude!

1193
01:17:07,600 --> 01:17:09,600
No mistakes now!

1194
01:17:11,577 --> 01:17:13,577
What do we do now?

1195
01:17:14,188 --> 01:17:16,188
I won't stop so easily.

1196
01:17:22,712 --> 01:17:24,712
Fall back now a bit,
you are in the lead!

1197
01:17:29,800 --> 01:17:31,800
Go, Go! Faster! Go, Faster!

1198
01:17:51,755 --> 01:17:53,755
Fuck off, man!

1199
01:17:54,500 --> 01:17:56,500
You bastard!

1200
01:18:11,100 --> 01:18:13,100
Okay?

1201
01:18:15,011 --> 01:18:18,051
Stop the Wave!

1202
01:18:18,940 --> 01:18:20,940
Stop the Wave!

1203
01:18:31,479 --> 01:18:33,479
We knew it!

1204
01:18:33,557 --> 01:18:35,557
Go, get all that flayers!
Everybody come here!

1205
01:18:59,799 --> 01:19:01,799
Why? What happened?

1206
01:19:12,569 --> 01:19:14,569
Are you crazy, or what?

1207
01:19:16,733 --> 01:19:18,733
Say, are you out of your mind?

1208
01:19:19,466 --> 01:19:21,466
What are you doing?

1209
01:19:21,873 --> 01:19:23,873
Sinan, what got into you?

1210
01:19:31,035 --> 01:19:33,035
Believe me, I... ...I
don't believe this.

1211
01:19:33,933 --> 01:19:36,058
Now you have brought the trouble here!

1212
01:19:36,233 --> 01:19:38,520
But I have not told them that they
should punch their opponents in the face!

1213
01:19:38,633 --> 01:19:40,808
But of course not, you are not
capable of doing that, right.

1214
01:19:41,061 --> 01:19:42,132
What are you trying to say to me?

1215
01:19:42,133 --> 01:19:45,171
You are enjoying that they think of you like of some
god at the class, they hang on every word of yours.

1216
01:19:45,533 --> 01:19:46,932
What are you saying?

1217
01:19:46,933 --> 01:19:50,316
Don't tell me that you don't like the fact that they do hang on
your every word as your students, who do you think who you are?

1218
01:19:50,433 --> 01:19:51,865
You completely missed the point!

1219
01:19:51,866 --> 01:19:54,592
The students see you as an example and
you manipulate them for your own cause!

1220
01:19:54,933 --> 01:19:57,700
There is only your ego trip,
don't you actually realize that?

1221
01:19:57,833 --> 01:19:59,732
Do you know what I believe, I
believe you are just damn jealous.

1222
01:19:59,733 --> 01:20:00,332
What?

1223
01:20:00,333 --> 01:20:03,697
Yes, jealous, because they don't see you as
example, despite your prestigious diplomas.

1224
01:20:03,933 --> 01:20:06,133
Yes, now this narrow-minded pedagogy will
show you how the things should be done.

1225
01:20:06,477 --> 01:20:08,477
Oh, narrow-minded, THAT is the problem.

1226
01:20:08,533 --> 01:20:10,472
Yes, that's what you think of me!

1227
01:20:10,473 --> 01:20:14,233
Graduated two times, diplomas in sports
and Political Science, what is it good for?

1228
01:20:14,448 --> 01:20:16,132
I did not know that the
problem lies so deep.

1229
01:20:16,133 --> 01:20:18,133
Oh you didn't know that the
problem lies so deep, right?

1230
01:20:18,336 --> 01:20:23,502
At least I don't have to take antidepressants every
morning because I have fucking fear of going to school!

1231
01:20:35,555 --> 01:20:38,206
Anke... Anke, wait.

1232
01:20:40,591 --> 01:20:42,349
- I did not mean that.
- You did.

1233
01:20:42,350 --> 01:20:44,156
You said, and you meant it!

1234
01:20:44,157 --> 01:20:47,480
For the last few days you
are really such an asshole.

1235
01:20:47,481 --> 01:20:49,481
Just leave me alone!

1236
01:20:56,682 --> 01:20:58,132
Karo, wait for me!

1237
01:20:58,133 --> 01:20:59,052
What was that earlier...

1238
01:20:59,053 --> 01:21:00,998
...have you gone crazy, or what?

1239
01:21:00,999 --> 01:21:02,150
You can not do that?

1240
01:21:02,151 --> 01:21:03,865
Who do you think you are?
Are you drunk, or what?

1241
01:21:03,866 --> 01:21:07,008
You better ask yourself, what is actually going on
with you? What happened today in the swimming pool?

1242
01:21:07,299 --> 01:21:09,154
It was full for the first time.

1243
01:21:09,155 --> 01:21:10,132
And the brawl?

1244
01:21:10,133 --> 01:21:12,083
That happened only
because of this shit here!

1245
01:21:12,084 --> 01:21:13,532
You really don't
understand anything, do you?

1246
01:21:13,533 --> 01:21:15,638
We would have win if you
had not mess up everything.

1247
01:21:16,542 --> 01:21:18,259
And that has annoyed you, right?

1248
01:21:18,260 --> 01:21:20,260
It would have been my
show for the first time.

1249
01:21:20,883 --> 01:21:22,234
Idiot.

1250
01:21:22,235 --> 01:21:23,862
- Karo!
- Leave me alone!

1251
01:21:23,863 --> 01:21:25,863
...do wait!

1252
01:21:35,783 --> 01:21:37,783
Do not touch me.

1253
01:21:38,444 --> 01:21:40,444
- Do not touch me!
- Karo.

1254
01:21:42,634 --> 01:21:44,634
Go away!

1255
01:22:25,469 --> 01:22:27,469
Marco, what are you doing here?

1256
01:22:29,236 --> 01:22:30,610
I'm in a deep shit.

1257
01:22:30,611 --> 01:22:32,611
Come in.

1258
01:22:36,686 --> 01:22:38,686
What's happening?

1259
01:22:40,408 --> 01:22:41,898
I...

1260
01:22:41,899 --> 01:22:43,899
I've hit Karo.

1261
01:22:44,022 --> 01:22:46,022
You did what?

1262
01:22:46,344 --> 01:22:47,754
I've beaten Karo.

1263
01:22:47,755 --> 01:22:49,755
Why?

1264
01:22:51,799 --> 01:22:53,799
I do really don't know.

1265
01:22:54,444 --> 01:22:56,444
We had an argue because...

1266
01:22:57,359 --> 01:22:59,657
This whole shit has totally changed me!

1267
01:23:01,135 --> 01:23:02,434
I love Karo!

1268
01:23:02,435 --> 01:23:04,435
And I've beaten her anyway.

1269
01:23:04,933 --> 01:23:07,908
This pseudo-discipline,
this is all Fascist shit!

1270
01:23:08,533 --> 01:23:10,533
You have to quit.

1271
01:23:11,269 --> 01:23:13,269
Rainer.

1272
01:23:16,151 --> 01:23:17,991
I have to think about it.

1273
01:23:17,992 --> 01:23:19,727
You have to quit.

1274
01:23:19,728 --> 01:23:22,333
- Immediately!
- Don't tell me what should I do.

1275
01:23:36,735 --> 01:23:39,143
Yes, I... I know, Mrs. Kohlhage.

1276
01:23:39,537 --> 01:23:41,444
I know, I know, yes.

1277
01:23:41,445 --> 01:23:43,445
I don't want just to make
bad things look better.

1278
01:23:44,404 --> 01:23:46,404
Yes, I do accept full responsibility.

1279
01:23:46,534 --> 01:23:48,295
But I must talk once
again with my students.

1280
01:23:48,296 --> 01:23:50,988
Only thing I am asking for is
to have a little trust in me.

1281
01:24:05,992 --> 01:24:07,732
<i>Hey guys, just arrived.</i>

1282
01:24:07,733 --> 01:24:09,332
<i>Tomorrow, School hall, 12 o'clock.</i>

1283
01:24:09,333 --> 01:24:10,999
<i>It is about the future of The Wave.</i>

1284
01:24:11,000 --> 01:24:13,433
<i>Send this only to
members and sympathisers.</i>

1285
01:24:13,559 --> 01:24:15,559
Three exclamation marks?

1286
01:24:54,520 --> 01:24:56,841
<i>Saturday</i>

1287
01:25:12,734 --> 01:25:14,939
Mr Wenger, it's quarter past twelve.

1288
01:25:16,092 --> 01:25:18,305
Then lock the doors, I
don't want to be disturbed.

1289
01:25:18,531 --> 01:25:20,433
OK.

1290
01:25:20,434 --> 01:25:23,729
Is it okay, if I stand in front
of you while you're speaking?

1291
01:25:24,308 --> 01:25:26,208
Then I have better overview of the hall.

1292
01:25:26,209 --> 01:25:28,209
I don't mind.

1293
01:25:35,036 --> 01:25:37,036
If everything is fine with you?

1294
01:25:39,833 --> 01:25:41,266
Okay, then lock the entrance.

1295
01:25:41,267 --> 01:25:44,133
Mr Wenger wishes not to be disturbed
during his speech, you got it?

1296
01:25:45,435 --> 01:25:47,435
Everybody get in now,
we are about to start!

1297
01:26:15,539 --> 01:26:19,333
<i>Actually, I always had everything
that I wanted, clothes, money etc...</i>

1298
01:26:19,648 --> 01:26:21,648
<i>...but what I had the
most was a boredom.</i>

1299
01:26:21,789 --> 01:26:23,032
These are my words.

1300
01:26:23,033 --> 01:26:25,033
<i>But the last few days
have been real fun.</i>

1301
01:26:26,540 --> 01:26:30,617
<i>It is no longer about who the most
beautiful or the best or the most successful.</i>

1302
01:26:31,234 --> 01:26:33,234
<i>The Wave has made us all equal.</i>

1303
01:26:35,639 --> 01:26:38,833
<i>Race, religion and social
status plays no role anymore.</i>

1304
01:26:39,704 --> 01:26:41,704
<i>We all belong to one movement.</i>

1305
01:26:41,905 --> 01:26:43,905
<i>The Wave gives us new meaning.</i>

1306
01:26:43,936 --> 01:26:46,160
<i>Ideals for which it
is worth to stand up.</i>

1307
01:26:46,858 --> 01:26:48,688
<i>I had bullied other students before.</i>

1308
01:26:48,689 --> 01:26:51,506
<i>If I really think back about
myself, it was really retarded of me.</i>

1309
01:26:51,908 --> 01:26:54,307
<i>It is much better to
stand up for a noble cause.</i>

1310
01:26:55,339 --> 01:26:58,633
<i>When you can lean on somebody
else, you can achieve so much more.</i>

1311
01:26:59,009 --> 01:27:01,072
<i>I am ready step back
from my bad behaviour.</i>

1312
01:27:06,133 --> 01:27:08,017
As you probably all noticed...

1313
01:27:08,018 --> 01:27:11,957
...these are all excerpts from your essays
on the experience from the last week.

1314
01:27:12,635 --> 01:27:14,699
I am very impressed with what
The Wave had brought to you.

1315
01:27:15,091 --> 01:27:18,039
And that's why I also believe
this project should not simply end.

1316
01:27:22,233 --> 01:27:24,807
- Rainer, what it this shit?
- Marco, do sit.

1317
01:27:24,808 --> 01:27:26,832
Yes but... Man, people think...

1318
01:27:26,983 --> 01:27:28,983
I've told you to sit down!

1319
01:27:31,871 --> 01:27:33,871
For several years the
Germany is going downhill!

1320
01:27:34,283 --> 01:27:36,283
We are the losers from globalization...

1321
01:27:36,433 --> 01:27:38,997
...but the politics tries to prove,
that struggling more and more...

1322
01:27:39,436 --> 01:27:41,436
...is the only way out of crisis.

1323
01:27:41,473 --> 01:27:43,761
But politicians are
puppets of the economy!

1324
01:27:44,434 --> 01:27:46,432
The unemployment rate should fall!

1325
01:27:46,433 --> 01:27:48,533
We are also world champion in exports!

1326
01:27:48,966 --> 01:27:50,932
But in reality...

1327
01:27:50,933 --> 01:27:53,712
...the poor are getting poorer
and the rich are getting richer!

1328
01:27:56,713 --> 01:27:58,803
Once the major threat was the terrorism.

1329
01:27:59,555 --> 01:28:05,188
A terror that we have created ourselves, by
allowing unfairness in the rest of the world!

1330
01:28:06,033 --> 01:28:09,138
And while we are slowly but
surely ruining our planet...

1331
01:28:10,033 --> 01:28:12,522
...some super-rich people sit
somewhere and rub their hands.

1332
01:28:13,033 --> 01:28:16,633
Building space capsules for themselves to be
able to see the whole thing from high above!

1333
01:28:19,434 --> 01:28:21,434
Don't you all understand his intentions?

1334
01:28:21,535 --> 01:28:23,364
He wants to manipulate you all!

1335
01:28:23,365 --> 01:28:24,743
Its enough, sit down.

1336
01:28:24,744 --> 01:28:27,033
You will not stop me from
telling the truth, Marco.

1337
01:28:27,333 --> 01:28:29,333
The Wave is the real problem!

1338
01:28:30,533 --> 01:28:34,833
No, The Wave is the only way that
that is able to make things better!

1339
01:28:35,249 --> 01:28:37,249
Because together we
can make thing happen!

1340
01:28:38,635 --> 01:28:40,635
We!

1341
01:28:41,488 --> 01:28:45,055
Today we have a chance
here to write the history!

1342
01:28:49,259 --> 01:28:52,888
Your girlfriend had turned you
against us. That is your problem.

1343
01:28:52,933 --> 01:28:54,933
- It is not true.
- Of course it's true!

1344
01:28:55,055 --> 01:28:57,237
She had completely
infected you with her shit.

1345
01:28:57,266 --> 01:28:58,932
You will not stop us!

1346
01:28:58,933 --> 01:29:01,497
From in here, The Wave should
reach the whole Germany!

1347
01:29:05,936 --> 01:29:07,936
And those who cross its path...

1348
01:29:07,952 --> 01:29:09,952
...will be washed away!

1349
01:29:11,236 --> 01:29:13,236
Exactly.

1350
01:29:15,333 --> 01:29:17,333
Bring forward the traitor!

1351
01:29:32,936 --> 01:29:35,633
Marco, Now I ask you in
front of everybody here:

1352
01:29:36,239 --> 01:29:38,834
Are you with us or against us?

1353
01:29:38,945 --> 01:29:40,945
Have you all completely
lost your mind, or what?

1354
01:29:41,530 --> 01:29:43,530
What should we do with the traitor?

1355
01:29:44,658 --> 01:29:46,658
What to do with traitor?

1356
01:29:49,238 --> 01:29:51,033
Bomber, you decide!

1357
01:29:51,034 --> 01:29:53,034
Come on, speak!

1358
01:29:54,858 --> 01:29:56,858
You have brought him up here.

1359
01:29:58,632 --> 01:30:00,532
Yeah, because you said so.

1360
01:30:00,533 --> 01:30:02,707
Yes, because I said, right?

1361
01:30:04,488 --> 01:30:06,488
And would you kill him, if I say so?

1362
01:30:08,341 --> 01:30:11,056
We can also hang or decapitate him!

1363
01:30:12,533 --> 01:30:14,628
Or maybe torture him until...

1364
01:30:14,933 --> 01:30:16,933
...he is committed to our rules!

1365
01:30:18,135 --> 01:30:20,135
That are the usual things
they do in a dictatorship.

1366
01:30:27,121 --> 01:30:29,121
Have you noticed what
had just happened here?

1367
01:30:31,133 --> 01:30:33,743
- Everything okay, Marco?
Yes, everything fine.

1368
01:30:37,933 --> 01:30:39,732
Can you remember...

1369
01:30:39,733 --> 01:30:41,921
...what question was floating
in the air since the last week?

1370
01:30:42,733 --> 01:30:44,902
Whether it was still possible
to have a dictatorship back here.

1371
01:30:47,333 --> 01:30:50,039
That was exactly that, fascism.

1372
01:30:53,321 --> 01:30:55,292
We all have taught we
are better than that.

1373
01:30:55,293 --> 01:30:57,293
Better than all the others.

1374
01:30:57,633 --> 01:30:59,633
And what is even worse...

1375
01:31:00,455 --> 01:31:03,332
...we have excluded from our community
all of these that didn't share our opinion.

1376
01:31:05,292 --> 01:31:07,292
We had them hurt.

1377
01:31:09,232 --> 01:31:11,232
I don't even want to know what
else would have we been capable of.

1378
01:31:16,534 --> 01:31:18,534
I must apologize to all of you.

1379
01:31:19,435 --> 01:31:21,435
We went too far.

1380
01:31:25,099 --> 01:31:27,099
I went too far.

1381
01:31:29,863 --> 01:31:31,863
The things will come to the end here.

1382
01:31:32,455 --> 01:31:34,964
And what does that mean
now... ...for The Wave?

1383
01:31:35,899 --> 01:31:37,899
That it is over.

1384
01:31:38,189 --> 01:31:39,932
Just like that?

1385
01:31:39,933 --> 01:31:41,933
Yes, just like that.

1386
01:31:42,432 --> 01:31:44,137
No, it is not over.

1387
01:31:44,138 --> 01:31:46,138
Yes Tim, it is over.

1388
01:31:46,159 --> 01:31:48,159
But not everything in The Wave is bad!

1389
01:31:49,152 --> 01:31:50,946
We all felt that.

1390
01:31:50,947 --> 01:31:53,232
Yes, we made some mistakes,
but nothing we can not correct!

1391
01:31:53,699 --> 01:31:55,232
No Dennis...

1392
01:31:55,233 --> 01:31:57,233
...some things you can not correct.

1393
01:31:59,443 --> 01:32:01,443
I want you all to go home now.

1394
01:32:02,148 --> 01:32:04,261
There are certainly things
that you should think about.

1395
01:32:22,534 --> 01:32:24,534
- Maja, I...
- Leave me alone.

1396
01:32:27,535 --> 01:32:29,230
Stop!

1397
01:32:29,231 --> 01:32:31,262
All remain at your seat
and leave the doors!

1398
01:32:31,933 --> 01:32:33,933
Nobody goes home!

1399
01:32:39,432 --> 01:32:41,705
- Put the gun away.
- You have lied to us.

1400
01:32:44,535 --> 01:32:47,149
The Wave lives, it is not dead!

1401
01:32:48,731 --> 01:32:51,876
Everybody say: "The Wave lives!

1402
01:32:52,888 --> 01:32:54,888
That is only a gas-gun.

1403
01:33:03,455 --> 01:33:05,311
Yes...

1404
01:33:05,312 --> 01:33:07,238
Now you take me seriously!

1405
01:33:07,239 --> 01:33:09,239
Do you think that I don't know
that you had always picked on me.

1406
01:33:11,433 --> 01:33:13,433
And you all had fucked with me.

1407
01:33:18,999 --> 01:33:20,999
The Wave...

1408
01:33:21,266 --> 01:33:23,266
...it was my life.

1409
01:33:28,687 --> 01:33:31,423
Tim, calm down.

1410
01:33:33,634 --> 01:33:35,634
Calm down.

1411
01:33:35,635 --> 01:33:37,635
Put the gun away.

1412
01:33:40,451 --> 01:33:43,299
Another step further and I
will shoot you in the face.

1413
01:33:44,637 --> 01:33:46,637
And then?

1414
01:33:47,485 --> 01:33:49,403
What then?

1415
01:33:49,404 --> 01:33:52,488
Then, there is no more Mr
Wenger, who can lead your Wave.

1416
01:33:54,410 --> 01:33:56,410
Is that what you want?

1417
